The paper deals with distributed parameter estimation in sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, the focus on nonlinear observation models and noisy inter-sensor communication suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under Information Theory (cs.IT), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Machine Learning (cs.MA). Additionally, the use of consensus-based algorithms and stochastic approximation theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Learning (cs.LG).
